Whosoever cometh to me, and heareth my sayings, and doeth them, I will shew you to whom he is like: 48 He is like a man which built an house, and digged deep, and laid the founda
tion on a rock: and when the flood arose, the stream beat vehemently upon that house, and could not shake it: for it was founded upon a rock.}{\b\f1\cf1\insrsid4270005\charrsid4270005 
\par }{\cf1\insrsid4270005 
\par It takes great effort and perseverance to \'93dig deep\'94. A deep foundation will stand, and a shallow one will eventually be broken. }{\cf1\insrsid1722989 This deep digging includes the searching of the scriptures, to understand 
the depth of the profundity of their meaning, and also the searching of the conscience. }{\cf1\insrsid4270005 Of course, the rock upon which we build is Christ: 
\par }\pard \qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid10765703 {\cf1\insrsid4270005 
\par }\pard \qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid1722989 {\cf1\insrsid1722989 \'93}{\cf1\insrsid1722989\charrsid1722989 For other foundation can no man lay than that is laid, which is Jesus Christ.}{\cf1\insrsid1722989 \'94}{
\cf1\insrsid1722989\charrsid1722989  (1Co}{\cf1\insrsid1722989 r}{\cf1\insrsid1722989\charrsid1722989  3:11)}{\cf1\insrsid4270005 
