\par }\pard \qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid1722989 {\cf1\insrsid15425295 
\par }\pard \qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid1722989 {\cf1\insrsid14636640 
\par }{\cf1\insrsid15425295 At our present time, as we are beginning to actual
ly build our new temple (after months of prayer, planning and fund raising),  these words remind me of our present efforts. As your pastor, despite my own limitations, I have attempted to make the foundation of our church to be the rock that is Christ. I 
am not speaking of  the concrete that will be poured this week or next, but the spiritual life of our community. Without spirit, the body is dead. Without effort and perseverance 
in our personal lives, we cannot expect God to bless our corporate lives in St Nicholas Russian Orthodox Church. 
\par }{\cf1\insrsid14751377 
\par I question myself daily, whether I am \'93digging deep\'94, and helping to provide a deep foundation for my small flock. I hope that you do this also. This \'93digging\'94 consists of daily prayer for all of you, the searching 
of the scriptures, and my personal effort to be a better person. Everything we do privately affects our community corporately. If I do not pray with so much attention on a certain day, I weaken our community. The same is true for everyone 
in the community. Our fasting, and prayer, and efforts to follow the commandments are both personal and corporate. 
\par 
\par The most important change I have made since we have begun seriously to talk of building has been to have a }{\ul\cf1\insrsid14751377\charrsid14636640 weekday Divine liturgy}{\cf1\insrsid14751377 
. We began this custom the week after Nativity this year, and have not failed to celebrate a Divine Liturgy at least once during the week}{\cf1\insrsid14636640  (on Wednesday at the beginning, now on Thursday). }{\cf1\insrsid14751377  }{
\cf1\insrsid14636640 S}{\cf1\insrsid14751377 ince then, with the one exception of when I was serving at our Diocesan Cathedral in Des Plain}{\cf1\insrsid14636640 e}{\cf1\insrsid14751377 s, IL, for their patronal feast. Of course, at that liturgy, I ma
de sure to commemorate everyone in the pro}{\cf1\insrsid14636640 s}{\cf1\insrsid14751377 kimidie. 
\par 
\par We must continue to do all we can to make our building project successful}{\i\cf1\insrsid14751377\charrsid14636640 . It will not end when temple is finished}{\cf1\insrsid14751377 
. The building we are doing is to build up the body of Christ. A new temple is critical to our success, but more critical is our personal involvement in the life of Christ. If we struggle spiritually, we will succeed physically and financially.  }{
\cf1\insrsid14751377\charrsid1722989 
